column17: 750 W Power Consumption Teflon Coated Soleplate Temperature Control The Kenstar Smart is an efficient dry iron designed for great ironing results. The Non-stick Teflon coated soleplate of the Kenstar Smart dry iron gives a gliding effect on the fabric. This soleplate helps you to smooth out tough wrinkles easily. This Non-stick Teflon soleplate also protects your clothes by not allowing them to stick to the iron in case of any overheating. The handle on the Kenstar Smart dry iron is ergonomic and has a comfortable grip. The centrally placed power cord of this Kenstar appliance makes ironing effortless. The adjustable temperature control dial on the Kenstar Smart dry iron allows you to set variable temperatures for different kind of fabrics. Higher temperatures are recommended for clothes with a lot of wrinkles and lower temperatures for delicate materials. If you are unable to decide on the kind of fabric your dress is made of then determine the right temperature by ironing a part of your dress that is not visible when you wear it. Safety and Power The Kenstar Smart dry iron consumes a maximum power of 750 W for fast heating. It is recommended to use an iron with high power wattage for an improved performance. The Kenstar Smart dry iron features a thermostat indicator light for operational safety. This light indicates to you when the iron has reached the required temperature.
